<%# locals: event, user_rsvp

    Two regions with two jobs.

    The CONTROL is client-owned: no turbo stream re-renders it, because any
    re-render tore the sliding indicator out mid-transition and the fill
    snapped instead of moving (see segmented_controller.js). Its visual state
    hangs off aria-pressed so CSS does the work.

    The NOTE has its own id and is the only part the streams replace. It used
    to live inside the streamed region along with the control, and the original
    warning here still stands in spirit: one region, one id, one stream target.
    Splitting it any other way once dumped a second note form into the header.

    UNANSWERED rests on Maybe, deliberately faint and untickd. That distinction
    is load-bearing: a solid fill would tell someone they had answered maybe
    when no RSVP exists, and their host would still see them as unanswered.
    Nothing is written until they actually pick. %>
<% answered = user_rsvp.present? %>
<div id="event-rsvp-buttons" class="flex flex-col gap-2 sm:items-end">
  <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
    <span class="text-sm text-cream/60"><%= answered ? "Going?" : "Coming along?" %></span>

    <div class="relative inline-flex rounded-full border border-cream/20 bg-cream/5 p-1"
         role="group" aria-label="Your RSVP"
         data-controller="segmented"
         data-action="turbo:submit-end->segmented#submitEnd">
      <%# Sits behind the labels and carries the fill. Position and width are
          written by the controller; colour comes off data-fill. %>
      <span id="rsvp-indicator" aria-hidden="true" data-segmented-target="indicator"
            class="rsvp-indicator pointer-events-none absolute bottom-1 left-0 top-1 rounded-full"></span>

      <% %w[yes maybe no].each do |answer| %>
        <%# ALWAYS the same action, whether or not an RSVP exists: this control
            is never re-rendered, so its form can't switch to an update path
            after the first answer. The endpoint is idempotent for that reason
            (see EventRsvpsController#create). %>
        <%= button_to event_event_rsvps_path(event), method: :post, params: { status: answer },
            aria: { pressed: (answered && user_rsvp.status == answer) },
            data: { answer: answer,
                    resting: (!answered && answer == "maybe" ? "true" : nil),
                    segmented_target: "option", action: "segmented#pick" },
            class: "rsvp-option relative z-10 cursor-pointer inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 " \
                   "rounded-full px-4 py-1.5 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors duration-200 " \
                   "focus:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-whiskey-300" do %>
          <%# Rendered for every option and shown by CSS on the pressed one, so
              choosing never has to build markup in JavaScript. %>
          <svg class="rsvp-tick h-3.5 w-3.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20" aria-hidden="true">
            <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
          </svg>
          <%= answer.capitalize %>
        <% end %>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <%= render "events/rsvp_note", event: event, user_rsvp: user_rsvp %>
</div>
